{
  "texts": [
    "Various datasets have been collected from MOOCs, LMSs, and other platforms, used for student's academic performance prediction.",
    "The mostly used dataset in the studies is the OULA dataset from MOOCs, which includes records of 32,593 students and 22 courses, and has been used in 13 studies among 15 (87%) that have used MOOCs datasets as shown in Figure 9.",
    "Other studies have used MOOCs datasets from the National Tsing Hua University (NTHU) and FutureLearn datasets.",
    "Moreover, LMSs private datasets as shown in Figure 10 Predicting student's academic performance relies on extracting various features from the VLE's datasets.",
    "OULAD, is the most commonly used dataset from MOOCs, which contains various features such as demographic, previous, and current academic performance, course-related information, and learning behavioral/activity features."
  ]
}